Title: "Data Transformation: Pivotting"

Overview:
The relig_income dataset contains information about income distribution across different religious groups. Each row represents a specific religion, and the columns represent different income categories along with the count of individuals belonging to that religion falling into each income category.

Variables:
religion: Name of the religious group.
income categories: Various income categories.
count: Number of individuals belonging to the religion falling into each income category.
Usage:
This dataset can be used for analyzing income disparities among religious groups, exploring the distribution of income across different income categories, 
and investigating potential correlations between religion and income.
